name: Thurston County Public Health Medical Reserve Corp
notes:
This is a Pfizer vaccination event for anyone age 12 and older. 

• This is a walk-in clinic at Griffin Middle School located at 6530 33rd Ave NW, Olympia WA, 98502. The clinic is from 9:00AM - 12:00PM. • All minors 12 to 17 years old must receive parent or guardian consent to receive a COVID-19 vaccine. This must be done in PrepMod when registering for an appointment. Parents or guardians do not have to be present at the time of vaccination if they signed the consent form online during registration. • Please bring a form of identification with you to your appointment - ID card, passport, or other document with your name and birthday on it. • Wear a short-sleeved shirt, but dress with layers if necessary. • Waiting at least 15 minutes after vaccination is required.
If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Ash Way Park & Ride DRIVE THROUGH - COVID Vaccine Site

address.street1: Ash Way Park & Ride DRIVE THROUGH: 16327 Ash Way

notes:
**THIS IS A PFIZER CLINIC**
Starting May 13, 2021, everyone 12 and older in Washington is eligible for COVID-19 vaccination.

Please also note that, you must be 12 or older for the Pfizer vaccine. Any minors receiving the vaccine will need a parent or guardian *physically present* to sign the consent form. 

Please arrive no more than 10 minutes prior to your appointment time. Expect to stay between 15-30 minutes after you receive your vaccine to monitor for any adverse reaction. Medical staff will be on hand. A mask must be worn at all times during the appointment, and please wear clothing with short or loose sleeves.

****IF YOU ARE SCHEDULING YOUR 2ND DOSE APPOINTMENT, YOU MUST PROVIDE PROOF OF 1ST DOSE (example: vaccination card, medical record, myir.net immunization record)****
If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

notes: *** PFIZER VACCINATIONS!!!!***!!!!VACUNAS DE PRIMERA DOSIS PFIZER!!! The vaccination clinic will take place at the Toppenish Post Office Park during the Toppenish Pancake Breakfast and Parade.
